13:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Anyword and ContentBot share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Short Form, Templates, Tone Control. Where Anyword pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Team Collaboration and Browser Extension, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Anyword holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while ContentBot scores 5/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, ContentBot comes in at a lower starting price of $19/mo, while Anyword begins at $49/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Anyword's free tier and ContentBot's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
